1. create a device node in /dev and then use normal file I/O
cat /proc/devices to get the eudyptula major

mknod /dev/eudyptula c 240 0
chmod 666 /dev/eudyptula

2. in kenrel cannot touch user space address
copy_from_user and copy_to_user t touch the user space address.
cannot directly read or print user space parameter

3. donot use echo and cat to test the program

echo "7c1caf2f50d1" > /dev/eudyptula
cat /dev/eudyptula

4. please use the normal file API to test the program
open read write

5. sizeof(*str1) sizeof(str2) is differently
char str1[] = "7c1caf2f50d1";
char *str2 = "7c1caf2f50d1";
sizeof(str1) is 13
sizeof(str2) is 8
stzeof(*str2) is 1
but str1[10] = str2[10]

we can use len(str2) string.h to get the length of str2 
